refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
boolPharFileInfo->setCompressedBZIP2
This method causes the file referenced to be compressed using bzip2 compression. The bzip2 extension must be enabled to take advantage of this feature. In addition, if the file is already compressed using gzip compression, the zlib extension must be enabled in order to decompress the file As with all functionality that modifies the contents of a phar, the phar.readonly INI variable must be off in order to succeed.

  &reftitle.examples;



    A PharFileInfo->setCompressedBZIP2 example


<?php
$p = new Phar('my.phar');
$p['myfile.txt'] = 'hi';
$file = $p['myfile.txt'];
var_dump($file->isCompressedBZIP2());
$p['myfile.txt']->setCompressedBZIP2();
var_dump($file->isCompressedBZIP2());
?>


    &example.outputs;


bool(false)
bool(true)
